  "text": "Addition of water soluble starch at concentration of 1 g/100 ml to growth medium with added EOs had no influence on antimicrobial efficacy (P > 0.05) (Table 4) . However, bacterial counts were significantly higher (P < 0.05) with a further increase in starch concentration, with respect to samples with EOs only. At a starch concentration of 20 g/100 ml, counts of L. innocua or E. coli treated with oregano or clove oil at respective MICs, increased on average by approx. 1 log CFU/ml, compared with samples containing EOs only (P < 0.05), indicating a degree of inhibition by water soluble starch on the efficacy of the EOs (Table 4) . Previously, it was observed that the growth rate of L. monocytogenes treated with EOs decreased at high starch concentrations [CITATION_1] A Results are expressed as log CFU/ml (mean ± SD).",
